{"id": 5099, "title": "Ticket #5099: Implement pickling for ClassAds / ExprTree in python bindings", "description": "<blockquote>\nboost-python has support for python's serialization protocol (called \"pickling\"); we should implement the required methods so <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ClassAds\" title=\"Class Ads\">ClassAds</a></span> and expressions can be serialized by python.\n\n<p>This came up in the context of LIGO; they'd like to use the python multiprocessing module, which executes functions in a subprocess, serializes the results&amp;#65533;using pickling, and sends them back to the parent process.\n\n</p><p>Reference: <a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_35_0/libs/python/doc/v2/pickle.html\">http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_35_0/libs/python/doc/v2/pickle.html</a></p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jul-30 12:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/e1ac9c88ac80e27e6738dbcdd5ed512f59b1d0bb\">[45438]</a></span>: minor edit of 8.3.8 version history (Python picke module support) <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"defer\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5099\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5099'); return false;\" title=\"Implement pickling for ClassAds / ExprTree in python bindings\">#5099</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jun-16 22:10</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=